**What shipped** (`Bringr/WindowEnumeration.swift` + `BringrTests/WindowEnumerationTests.swift`, pbxproj IDs 0x2D–0x30):

- `WindowEnumerator` reports apps with normal, on-screen windows grouped front-to-back, behind a `WindowEnumerationSource` seam — mirroring the existing `WindowControlling` pattern. `CGWindowSource` is the live CoreGraphics conformer; `FakeWindowEnumerationSource` backs the tests.
- Models: `AppWindows` (per-app group with name + windows) and `WindowInfo` (stable `WindowID` whose token is `kCGWindowNumber`, plus title and computed owning `app`).
- "Normal window" filter drops Bringr itself, non-layer-0 surfaces (menu bar/dock/status items), invisible (alpha 0) and tiny helper windows; apps left with zero windows fall out, so menu-bar-only apps/agents are excluded for free.
- Titles are best-effort: `kCGWindowName` needs Screen Recording (a non-goal), so they're usually empty and fall back to `"Window N"` (US-006 permits index labels). Real titles are a clean later live-layer enrichment.
- AC4 timing: `lastDuration` + os_log record every call; measured ~0.7 ms for 8 apps live — far under the 16 ms summon budget.

**Gates:** build SUCCEEDED · swiftlint 0 violations · 25 tests pass (10 new). App launches stably.

**Flagged for later:** US-003's `WindowID` token (CG window number) differs from US-004 `LiveWindowSystem`'s enumeration-index token — US-010/011/012 must reconcile them before passing enumerator `WindowID`s to `WindowController`. Documented in `progress.md`. No commit created (engine handles that).

